originalSql:
SELECT 
    n.name AS actor_name,
    t.title AS movie_title,
    c.nr_order AS role_order,
    k.keyword AS movie_keyword,
    r.role AS role_type
FROM 
    cast_info c
JOIN 
    aka_name n ON c.person_id = n.person_id
JOIN 
    aka_title t ON c.movie_id = t.movie_id
JOIN 
    movie_keyword mk ON t.id = mk.movie_id
JOIN 
    keyword k ON mk.keyword_id = k.id
JOIN 
    role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
WHERE 
    t.production_year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2023
ORDER BY 
    t.production_year DESC, c.nr_order

    r.role AS role_type
FROM 
    cast_info c
JOIN 
    aka_name n ON c.person_id = n.person_id
JOIN 
    aka_title t ON c.movie_id = t.movie_id
JOIN 
    movie_keyword mk ON t.id = mk.movie_id
JOIN 
    keyword k ON mk.keyword_id = k.id
JOIN 
    role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
WHERE 
    t.production_year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2023
ORDER BY 
    t.production_year DESC, c.nr_order

SELECT COALESCE("t1"."ACTOR_NAME", "t1"."ACTOR_NAME") AS "ACTOR_NAME", "t1"."MOVIE_TITLE", "t1"."ROLE_ORDER", "t1"."MOVIE_KEYWORD", "t1"."ROLE_TYPE", "t1"."production_year"

FROM "role_type"
INNER JOIN ("aka_name" INNER JOIN "cast_info" ON "aka_name"."person_id" = "cast_info"."person_id") ON "role_type"."id" = "cast_info"."role_id"
INNER JOIN ((SELECT *
